TITLE: Persisting Webview State using getState and setState in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code runs inside a VS Code webview. It uses the `acquireVsCodeApi()` function to get access to the VS Code API. It retrieves previously saved state using `vscode.getState()`, updates a counter element, and periodically saves the updated count using `vscode.setState({ count })`, allowing the state (a JSON serializable object) to persist across webview visibility changes but not across panel destruction.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/api/extension-guides/webview.md#2025-04-23_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js
// Inside a webview script
const vscode = acquireVsCodeApi();

const counter = document.getElementById('lines-of-code-counter');

// Check if we have an old state to restore from
const previousState = vscode.getState();
let count = previousState ? previousState.count : 0;
counter.textContent = count;

setInterval(() => {
  counter.textContent = count++;
  // Update the saved state
  vscode.setState({ count });
}, 100);
```
```

