TITLE: Executing Commands with Arguments and Handling Results in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to execute the 'vscode.executeDefinitionProvider' command with document URI and position arguments, which returns a promise with a list of definitions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/api/extension-guides/command.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import * as vscode from 'vscode';

async function printDefinitionsForActiveEditor() {
  const activeEditor = vscode.window.activeTextEditor;
  if (!activeEditor) {
    return;
  }

  const definitions = await vscode.commands.executeCommand<vscode.Location[]>(
    'vscode.executeDefinitionProvider',
    activeEditor.document.uri,
    activeEditor.selection.active
  );

  for (const definition of definitions) {
    console.log(definition);
  }
}
```

