TITLE: Deleting Items using Redis in FastAPI
DESCRIPTION: A FastAPI route that deletes an item from a Redis database by its ID. It checks if the item exists, retrieves the item name, removes references in Redis hashes, and returns a success message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/docs/python/tutorial-fastapi.md#2025-04-23_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
@app.delete("/items/{item_id}")
def delete_item(item_id: int) -> dict[str, str]:
    if not redis_client.hexists(f"item_id:{item_id}", "item_id"):
        raise HTTPException(status_code=404, detail="Item not found.")
    else:
        item_name: str | None = redis_client.hget(f"item_id:{item_id}", "item_name")
        redis_client.hdel("item_name_to_id", f"{item_name}")
        redis_client.delete(f"item_id:{item_id}")
        return {"result": "Item deleted."}
```

