TITLE: Manually Adding VS Code APT Repository on Debian/Ubuntu
DESCRIPTION: Provides the necessary commands to manually download the Microsoft GPG key using `wget` and `gpg`, add it to the system's trusted keyrings (`/etc/apt/keyrings/`), create the APT source list file (`/etc/apt/sources.list.d/vscode.list`), and clean up the downloaded key file. Requires `wget` and `gpg` to be installed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/docs/setup/linux.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
sudo apt-get install wget gpg
wget -qO- https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | gpg --dearmor > packages.microsoft.gpg
sudo install -D -o root -g root -m 644 packages.microsoft.gpg /etc/apt/keyrings/packages.microsoft.gpg
echo "deb [arch=amd64,arm64,armhf signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/packages.microsoft.gpg] https://packages.microsoft.com/repos/code stable main" |sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/vscode.list > /dev/null
rm -f packages.microsoft.gpg
```

