TITLE: Configuring Build Task in tasks.json for MSVC (JSON)
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet defines a VS Code build task labeled "cl.exe build active file" designed to compile the currently active C++ file using MSVC (`cl.exe`). It's specifically configured for Windows environments where VS Code might not be launched from a Developer Command Prompt. It achieves this by setting the shell option to use `cmd.exe` to first execute `VsDevCmd.bat` (initializing the necessary environment variables like `INCLUDE`) and then invoking the `cl.exe` compiler with flags for debugging symbols (`/Zi`), C++ exception handling (`/EHsc`), specifying the output executable name (`/Fe:`), and the input source file (`${file}`). It also includes a problem matcher (`$msCompile`) to parse build errors.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/docs/cpp/config-msvc.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    "version": "2.0.0",
    "windows": {
        "options": {
            "shell": {
                "executable": "cmd.exe",
                "args": [
                    "/C",
                    // The path to VsDevCmd.bat depends on the version of Visual Studio you have installed.
                    "\"C:/Program Files (x86)/Microsoft Visual Studio/2019/Community/Common7/Tools/VsDevCmd.bat\"",
                    "&&"
                ]
            }
        }
    },
    "tasks": [
        {
            "type": "shell",
            "label": "cl.exe build active file",
            "command": "cl.exe",
            "args": [
                "/Zi",
                "/EHsc",
                "/Fe:",
                "${fileDirname}\\\${fileBasenameNoExtension}.exe",
                "${file}"
            ],
            "problemMatcher": [
                "$msCompile"
            ],
            "group": {
                "kind": "build",
                "isDefault": true
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

