TITLE: Implementing Django View with Name Parameter
DESCRIPTION: Defines a Django view function that handles the hello route, processes a name parameter with regex validation, and returns a formatted greeting with timestamp.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/docs/python/tutorial-django.md#2025-04-23_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
import re
from django.utils.timezone import datetime
from django.http import HttpResponse

def home(request):
    return HttpResponse("Hello, Django!")

def hello_there(request, name):
    now = datetime.now()
    formatted_now = now.strftime("%A, %d %B, %Y at %X")

    # Filter the name argument to letters only using regular expressions. URL arguments
    # can contain arbitrary text, so we restrict to safe characters only.
    match_object = re.match("[a-zA-Z]+", name)

    if match_object:
        clean_name = match_object.group(0)
    else:
        clean_name = "Friend"

    content = "Hello there, " + clean_name + "! It's " + formatted_now
    return HttpResponse(content)
```

