TITLE: Registering Virtual Document Provider in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of a TextDocumentContentProvider that manages virtual documents using a Map to store content. The provider handles URI manipulation to serve virtual document content for embedded languages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/api/language-extensions/embedded-languages.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const virtualDocumentContents = new Map<string, string>()

workspace.registerTextDocumentContentProvider('embedded-content', {
  provideTextDocumentContent: uri => {
    // Remove leading `/` and ending `.css` to get original URI
    const originalUri = uri.path.slice(1).slice(0, -4);
    const decodedUri = decodeURIComponent(originalUri);
    return virtualDocumentContents.get(decodedUri);
  }
})
```

