DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript snippet shows how to implement the `log` function (imported by the Wasm module) within a VS Code extension's `activate` function. It creates a VS Code output channel, defines a `service` object containing the `log` implementation, uses `calculator._.imports.create` (from the `@vscode/wasm-component-model` generated bindings) to prepare the import object, and passes it to `WebAssembly.instantiate` to make the function available to the Wasm module.
