TITLE: Authorizing Windows Host with User-Level Key (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: Appends the public SSH key to a user-level authorized_keys file on a Windows SSH host using a Bash SSH command that invokes PowerShell remotely. It first creates the .ssh directory if missing, sets up permissions, and adds the public key to the appropriate file. Designed for cases where the user doesn't have administrator-level access or needs user-scope key authorization.
