TITLE: Configuring Notebook Preloads in VS Code package.json (JSONC)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the proposed `notebookPreload` contribution point in a VS Code extension's `package.json` to specify JavaScript preload scripts for particular notebook types (like 'jupyter-notebook'). These scripts, identified by their `entrypoint`, are executed before any notebook renderer scripts for the specified `type`. This feature requires enabling the `contribNotebookStaticPreloads` proposed API.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/release-notes/v1_73.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: jsonc
CODE:
```
{
    "contributes": {
        "notebookPreload": [
            {
                "type": "jupyter-notebook", // Type of notebook for the preload script
                "entrypoint": "./path/to/preload.js"
