TITLE: Implementing Notebook Will-Save Event Handler in VS Code Extensions
DESCRIPTION: Example of registering a listener for the onWillSaveNotebookDocument event in VS Code. This proposed API event fires before a notebook document is saved, allowing extensions to perform actions like cleaning up notebook cell outputs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/release-notes/v1_77.md#2025-04-23_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
vscode.workspace.onWillSaveNotebookDocument(e => {
    if (event.reason == vscode.NotebookDocumentSaveReason.Manual) {
      event.waitUntil(new Promise((resolve) => {
        const notebookEdit = new vscode.NotebookEdit(...);
        const edit = new vscode.WorkspaceEdit();
        edit.set(event.document.uri, [notebookEdit]);
        resolve([edit]);
      }));
    }
});
```

