TITLE: Configuration Change Handler in TypeScript Language Server
DESCRIPTION: Handles configuration changes in the language server by clearing cached settings and revalidating all open documents. Supports both configuration capability modes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-docs/blob/main/api/language-extensions/language-server-extension-guide.md#2025-04-23_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
connection.onDidChangeConfiguration(change => {
  if (hasConfigurationCapability) {
    // Reset all cached document settings
    documentSettings.clear();
  } else {
    globalSettings = <ExampleSettings>(
      (change.settings.languageServerExample || defaultSettings)
    );
  }

  // Revalidate all open text documents
  documents.all().forEach(validateTextDocument);
});
